                    android:text="     I am thinking  why we  call  our  age as ‘the  age  of life’? How  many of us are truly living? Because as Buddha says ‘Without health, life is not life, it is only languor and suffering an image of death. Of course , technology  has made us  realize  most of our  hopes. We have all the things required for our well being, but with our utter negligence towards basic hygiene, we have no sense of well being. Yes, we have wired technology, wireless technology. But amidst all this, our health is in haywire. So, we must rewire our lifestyles.
                    "
